race.comment: KIWI HARMONY (11) has been out of the money at two runs back, but they were in stronger races than this. With those runs under the belt and the plum draw here, she looks the testing material. BRUTIFY (9) showed good early dash last time out and led for most of the way before being claimed and finishing half a length away in second over 1200m at Terang. This track can often suit on-pacers, so she needs to go in everything. KIJIVU (2) is a four-start maiden who could only manage to finish fifth at his latest appearance over 1000m at Camperdown but he's fitter here and 1200m should suit. HELLOFACURY (8) drifted back on debut last start then came home soundly to be beaten 2.75 lengths into fifth over 1110m, which importantly was at this track.
